commit.message: Fix up small README.md typo
Update README
travis: add `libevent-dev` as build-dep
Add `gen` to .gitignore
Drop confusing `reddns` module
Bump year in `Copyright` mark, ouch that is ancient soft!
Add `dnsu2t` module to convert DNS/UDP to DNS/TCP
More reserver IPv4 addresses
Version bump - v0.5
Link against `levent_core` when that is enough
Emit better errors from config file parser
Fix typo
New link to `Netfilter-packet-flow` image
Add travis-ci to smoke-test MacOSX builds

Specify required libevent version in README. Closes #85

libevent-2.0.x is required since 14ff78d.

Implement `redsocks_conn_max` option, simplify accept-backoff

Sophisticated accept-backoff is not required, it's ONLY purpose is to
protect against busy-loop when `redsocks_conn_max` does not match
RLIMIT_NOFILE.
Fix cleanup order to avoid EBADF from epoll_ctl

Add `on_proxy_fail` to inform user's browser about sort of failure

Use the feature with care, enable it only for HTTP port to avoid
confusion, no client protocol detection is done at the moment.
Log dropped clients when http-proxy reply is too long
Add tests for authentication failure
Test that `nonce` reuse in http-digest actually works
Add protocol latency tests
Make `netns exec` call easier in tests
Update link to Archlinux AUR. Fixes #82
Fix memory leak in Basic http-auth
Add smoke tests
Fix typo introduced in 003765ba, fixes #81
